body:
If a doc comment of a trait item begins with a code block, it will be changed to inline code in implementations of that trait, which leads to weird formatting.

### Example

```rust
pub trait TraitExample {
    /// Some text.
    ///
    /// ```
    /// let a = 0;
    /// ```
    fn a() {}

    /// ```
    /// let b = 0;
    /// ```
    fn b() {}

    /// ```rust
    /// let c = 0;
    /// ```
    fn c() {}

    /// ```
    /// // Comment `example`.
    /// let d = 0;
    /// ```
    fn d() {}
}

pub struct StructExample;

impl TraitExample for StructExample {}

```

Here is what it looks like in the implementation for `StructExample`:

![2020-06-18-154158_1542x547_scrot](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/41170571/85027444-3a45c980-b17a-11ea-8474-167a582db076.png)

- The docs for the method `a` work as expected.

- The code block of method `b` is changed to inline code.

- The code block of method `c` is also changed to inline code and the word `rust` is shown in the inline code instead of specifying the syntax. There is also a trailing whitespace which is not present in the original code block.

- In the docs of `d` the backticks of the word `example` end the main inline code.

While the inline code looks fine in simple examples (e.g. docs of method `b`), the format is confusing in most cases. The expected behaviour would probably be that the code block does **not** get converted to inline code.

### Example in `std`

Another example for this behaviour can be seen in the [`description`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/stable/std/error/trait.Error.html#method.description) method of `std::error::Error`. The docs of the method  begin with a code block and then get changed to inline code in the implementations.

Documentation in `std::error::Error`:

![2020-06-18-160734_1537x305_scrot](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/41170571/85030561-e0df9980-b17d-11ea-96c1-92afcaabe076.png)

Documentation of the implementation in `std::io::Error`:

![2020-06-18-160528_1517x191_scrot](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/41170571/85030243-7f1f2f80-b17d-11ea-8469-e8ad66b6aa9c.png)

More examples: `std::io::Error` ([stable](https://doc.rust-lang.org/stable/std/io/struct.Error.html#implementations), [nightly](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/std/io/struct.Error.html#implementations)), `std::num::ParseIntError` ([stable](https://doc.rust-lang.org/stable/std/num/struct.ParseIntError.html#implementations), [nightly](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/std/num/struct.ParseIntError.html#implementations)).

